==Funding==
{{Expand section|date=March 2011}}
WBC's travel expenses exceed $200,000 annually.<ref name=bbc>{{cite video |people=O'Connor, Geoffrey; [[Louis Theroux|Theroux, Louis]] |title=[[The Most Hated Family in America]] |publisher=BBC}}</ref> According to the [[Southern Poverty Law Center]], Westboro is funded entirely by its congregation and accepts no outside donations.<ref name="splc">{{cite web|title=Westboro Baptist Church|url=http://www.splcenter.org/get-informed/intelligence-files/groups/westboro-baptist-church|publisher=Southern Poverty Law Center|accessdate=March 5, 2011}}</ref> The church has received money from lawsuits and legal fees.<ref name="splc" /><ref name="shaw-yorkdispatch">Shaw, Andrew (March 3, 2011). [http://www.yorkdispatch.com/news/ci_17528821 "Marine's father responds to Supreme Court decision on Westboro Baptist"]. ''The York Dispatch''.{{dead link|date=October 2011}}</ref> For example, they sued the city of Topeka several times in the 1990s.<ref name="splc" /> WBC received $16,500, and is pursuing another $100,000, in legal fees for a case won in court.<ref name="shaw-yorkdispatch" /> The WBC is considered a nonprofit organization by the federal government, and is therefore exempt from paying taxes.<ref>{{cite news|last=Lowder|first=J. Bryan|title=Subsidized Hate|url=http://www.slate.com/id/2287335/|accessdate=March 5, 2011|newspaper=Slate|date=March 4, 2011}}</ref>

